{"title_page": "Designated Survivor (season 2)", "text_new": "{{Infobox television season\n| season_number        = 2\n| bgcolour             = #960018\n| image                = Designated Survivor season 2 poster.jpeg\n| caption              = Promotional poster\n| starring             = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Kiefer Sutherland]]\n* [[Natascha McElhone]]\n* [[Paulo Costanzo]]\n* [[Adan Canto]]\n* [[Italia Ricci]]\n* [[LaMonica Garrett]]\n* [[Zoe McLellan]]\n* [[Ben Lawson]]\n* [[Kal Penn]]\n* [[Maggie Q]]\n}}\n| country              = United States\n| num_episodes         = 22\n| network              = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2017|9|27}}\n| last_aired               = {{end date|2018|5|16}}\n<!-- | company              = {{Plainlist|\n*[[ABC Studios]]\n*[[Mark Gordon Company]]}} -->\n| prev_season          = [[Designated Survivor (season 1)|Season 1]]\n| next_season          = [[Designated Survivor (season 3)|Season 3]]\n| episode_list         = List of Designated Survivor episodes\n}}\n\nThe second season of the American [[political drama]] series ''[[Designated Survivor (TV series)|Designated Survivor]]'' was ordered on May 11, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2017/05/11/designated-survivor-renewed-season-2-abc/ |title=Designated Survivor Renewed at ABC |first1=Michael |last1=Ausiello |first2=Michael |last2=Ausiello |date=May 12, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170513150936/http://tvline.com/2017/05/11/designated-survivor-renewed-season-2-abc/ |archivedate=May 13, 2017 }}</ref> It premiered on September 27, 2017, and consisted of 22 episodes.<ref name=\"premiere date\">{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2017/07/24/abc-premiere-dates-fall-2017-greys-anatomy-scandal/|title=ABC Fall Premiere Dates: XL Grey's Return, Scandal's Swan Song and More|work=[[TVLine]]|last=Mitovich|first=Matt Webb|date=July 24, 2017|accessdate=July 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170727093459/http://tvline.com/2017/07/24/abc-premiere-dates-fall-2017-greys-anatomy-scandal/|archive-date=July 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The series is produced by [[ABC Studios]] and [[The Mark Gordon Company]], and is filmed in [[Toronto]] and [[Cambridge, Ontario|Cambridge]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://kitchener.ctvnews.ca/designated-survivor-films-season-finale-scene-in-cambridge-1.3847511|title=Designated Survivor films season finale scene in Cambridge|date=2018-03-17|work=Kitchener|access-date=2018-04-03|language=en-CA|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180403234714/https://kitchener.ctvnews.ca/designated-survivor-films-season-finale-scene-in-cambridge-1.3847511|archive-date=2018-04-03|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Ontario]], Canada.\n\n==Premise==\nOne year into office, President Thomas Kirkman juggles searching for the mastermind behind the attack on the [[United States Capitol|Capitol Building]], dealing with the day-to-day situations that take place at home and abroad, and surviving attacks against his administration.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n===Main===\n* [[Kiefer Sutherland]] as [[President of the United States|President]] Thomas \"Tom\" Kirkman<ref name=\"201PressRelease\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/listings/20170912abc02/|title=(#201) \"One Year In\"|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|accessdate=September 12, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Natascha McElhone]] as [[First Lady of the United States|First Lady]] Alexandra \"Alex\" Kirkman<ref name=\"201PressRelease\" />\n* [[Paulo Costanzo]] as White House Political Director Lyor Boone<ref name=\"201PressRelease\" />\n* [[Adan Canto]] as [[National Security Advisor (United States)|National Security Advisor]] Aaron Shore<ref name=\"201PressRelease\" />\n* [[Italia Ricci]] as [[White House Chief of Staff]] Emily Rhodes<ref name=\"201PressRelease\" />\n* [[LaMonica Garrett]] as [[United States Secret Service]] [[Special Agent]], Mike Ritter;<ref name=\"201PressRelease\" /> head of President Kirkman's Secret Service protection detail\n* [[Zoe McLellan]] as [[White House Counsel]] Kendra Daynes<ref name=\"201PressRelease\" />\n* [[Ben Lawson]] as [[Secret Intelligence Service]] (MI6) [[Intelligence Officer]], Damian Rennett<ref name=\"201PressRelease\" />\n* [[Kal Penn]] as [[White House Press Secretary]] Seth Wright<ref name=\"201PressRelease\" />\n* [[Maggie Q]] as [[Federal Bureau of Investigation]] (FBI) Special Agent Hannah Wells<ref name=\"201PressRelease\" />\n\n===Recurring===\n* [[Terry Serpico]] as Patrick Lloyd\n* [[Jake Epstein]] as Chuck Russink\n* [[Tanner Buchanan]] as Leo Kirkman, the President's son\n* [[Mckenna Grace]] as Penny Kirkman, the President's daughter\n* [[Reed Diamond]] as [[Director of the Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI Director]] John Foerstel\n* [[Geoff Pierson]] as [[United States Secretary of State|Secretary of State]] Cornelius Moss\n* [[Mykelti Williamson]] as [[Vice Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff|Vice Chairman]] Admiral Chernow\n* [[Kim Raver]] as Andrea Frost, aerospace engineer, tech billionaire, friend of Kirkman's<ref>{{cite web|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|title=Designated Survivor Stages 24 Reunion: Kim Raver Set for Big Season 2 Arc|url=http://tvline.com/2017/11/09/designated-survivor-kim-raver-season-2-cast-kiefer-sutherland-24/|work=TVline|accessdate=March 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180316123903/http://tvline.com/2017/11/09/designated-survivor-kim-raver-season-2-cast-kiefer-sutherland-24/|archive-date=March 16, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Breckin Meyer]] as Trey Kirkman, the President's brother<ref name=\"Deadline\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/11/designated-survivor-breckin-meyer-recur-season-2-1202212609/|title=\u2018Designated Survivor\u2019: Breckin Meyer Set To Recur In Season 2|date=November 20, 2017|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=November 24, 2017|first=Denise|last=Petski|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171122015919/http://deadline.com/2017/11/designated-survivor-breckin-meyer-recur-season-2-1202212609/|archive-date=November 22, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Aunjanue Ellis]] as [[Mayor of the District of Columbia|Mayor]], later [[Vice President of the United States|Vice President]] Ellenor Darby\n* [[Bonnie Bedelia]] as Eva Booker\n* [[Michael J. Fox]] as Ethan West<ref name=\"Hipes\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2018/01/michael-j-fox-designated-survivor-guest-role-abc-1202239957/|title=Michael J. Fox Joining \u2018Designated Survivor\u2019 For Arc|date=January 10, 2018|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=January 10, 2018|first=Patrick|last=Hipes|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180110193505/http://deadline.com/2018/01/michael-j-fox-designated-survivor-guest-role-abc-1202239957/|archive-date=January 10, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Nora Zehetner]] as Valeria Poriskova, Russian intelligence agent<ref>{{cite web|last=Petski|first=Denise|title=\u2018Designated Survivor\u2019: Nora Zehetner Set To Recur On ABC Drama Series|url=http://deadline.com/2018/03/designated-survivor-nora-zehetner-recur-abc-drama-series-1202346189/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=March 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180322021914/http://deadline.com/2018/03/designated-survivor-nora-zehetner-recur-abc-drama-series-1202346189/|archive-date=March 22, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Guest===\n* [[Tim Busfield]] as Dr. Adam Louden, the President's therapist\n\n==Episodes==\n<onlyinclude>{{Episode table|background=#960018 |overall=5|season=5|title=23|director=15|writer=29|airdate=14|viewers=9|country=US|episodes=\n{{Episode list/sublist|Designated Survivor (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 22\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = One Year In\n |DirectedBy      = [[Chris Grismer]]\n |WrittenBy       = Keith Eisner \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|9|27}}\n |Viewers         = 5.50<ref name=\"2.01\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/wednesday-final-ratings-s