ignated Survivor\u2019: Keith Eisner Set As Showrunner, Pending Season 2 Renewal|website=Deadline Hollywood|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=May 2, 2017|accessdate=July 18, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170704222030/http://deadline.com/2017/05/designated-survivor-keith-eisner-new-showrunner-season-2-renewal-1202082116/|archive-date=July 4, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Eisner will be the fourth showrunner for the show, replacing [[Jeff Melvoin]], who was hired as showrunner in December 2016, taking over for [[Jon Harmon Feldman]].<ref name=\"melvoin\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/12/new-showrunner-for-designated-survivor-1201864262/ |title=\u2018Designated Survivor\u2019 Taps New Showrunner As Jon Harmon Feldman Exits |last=Licoln |first=Ross |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=December 4, 2016 |accessdate=March 20, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222191243/http://deadline.com/2016/12/new-showrunner-for-designated-survivor-1201864262/ |archivedate=December 22, 2016 }}</ref> The show's original showrunner [[Amy B. Harris]] stepped down due to creative differences after the series' official pickup in February 2016.<ref name=\"Order1\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/05/kiefer-sutherland-abc-designated-survivor-series-pickup-trailer-jon-feldman-showrunner-1201750838/ |title=Kiefer Sutherland ABC Drama \u2018Designated Survivor\u2019 Gets Formal Series Pickup, First Trailer; Eyes Jon Feldman As Showrunner |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=May 6, 2016 |accessdate=May 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160511173601/http://deadline.com/2016/05/kiefer-sutherland-abc-designated-survivor-series-pickup-trailer-jon-feldman-showrunner-1201750838/ |archivedate=May 11, 2016 }}</ref> \n\nOn June 22, 2017, cast member [[Virginia Madsen]] announced that she would not be returning for the second season as Kimble Hookstraten as she commented \"I guess they had other stories to tell. It's a big show so I wish them well.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/designated-survivor-virginia-madsen-will-not-return-season-2-1016013|title='Designated Survivor': Virginia Madsen Will Not Return for Season 2|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|date=June 22, 2017|accessdate=July 18, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170723061927/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/designated-survivor-virginia-madsen-will-not-return-season-2-1016013|archive-date=July 23, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> After the first-season finale, Sutherland announced that the show would add three new characters for the second season. Two of the character descriptions was \"a \"fiery\" female White House Counsel and a \"ruggedly handsome\" [[Secret Intelligence Service|MI6]] operative who crosses paths with Hannah.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2017/06/08/hawaii-five-0-season-8-spoilers-casting-new-series-regular-female/|title=Matt's Inside Line: Scoop on Five-0, Killjoys, Arrow, Designated Survivor, Zoo, Stranger Things, Riverdale and More|work=[[TVLine]]|last=Mitovich|first=Matt Webb|date=June 8, 2017|accessdate=July 18, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170718171444/http://tvline.com/2017/06/08/hawaii-five-0-season-8-spoilers-casting-new-series-regular-female/|archive-date=July 18, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> [[TVLine]] announced on June 29, 2017, that [[Paulo Costanzo]] had been cast as a series regular role as Lyor Boone, the new White House Political Director.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2017/06/29/designated-survivor-paulo-costanzo-season-2-lyor-boone/|title=Designated Survivor Enlists Royal Pains' Paulo Costanzo as New Regular|work=[[TVLine]]|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=June 29, 2017|accessdate=July 18, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170713201916/http://tvline.com/2017/06/29/designated-survivor-paulo-costanzo-season-2-lyor-boone/|archive-date=July 13, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]'' reported on July 17, 2017, that [[Ben Lawson]] had been cast as the series regular character Damian Rennett, an MI6 operative.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/07/designated-survivor-ben-lawson-cast-series-regular-season-2-1202129188/|title=\u2018Designated Survivor\u2019: Ben Lawson Cast As Series Regular In Season 2|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=July 17, 2017|accessdate=July 18, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170715233744/http://deadline.com/2017/07/designated-survivor-ben-lawson-cast-series-regular-season-2-1202129188/|archive-date=July 15, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In the same month, it was announced that [[Zoe McLellan]] was cast in a series regular role as attorney and White House counsel, Kendra Daynes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/07/designated-survivor-zoe-mclellan-joins-season-2-cast-abc-kiefer-sutherland-1202130954/|title=\u2018Designated Survivor\u2019: Zoe McLellan Joins Season 2 Of ABC\u2019s Kiefer Sutherland Drama|date=July 18, 2017|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=March 21, 2018|first=Erik|last=Pedersen|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303094439/http://deadline.com/2017/07/designated-survivor-zoe-mclellan-joins-season-2-cast-abc-kiefer-sutherland-1202130954/|archive-date=March 3, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> In November 2017, [[Kim Raver]] was cast in the recurring role of engineer and space entrepreneur, Andrea Frost.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|title=Designated Survivor Stages 24 Reunion: Kim Raver Set for Big Season 2 Arc|url=http://tvline.com/2017/11/09/designated-survivor-kim-raver-season-2-cast-kiefer-sutherland-24/|date=November 9, 2017|work=TVline|accessdate=March 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180316123903/http://tvline.com/2017/11/09/designated-survivor-kim-raver-season-2-cast-kiefer-sutherland-24/|archive-date=March 16, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In January 2018, [[Michael J. Fox]] was cast in the recurring role of Washington attorney and [[special prosecutor]], Ethan West.<ref name=\"Hipes\"/> In March 2018, [[Nora Zehetner]] was cast in the recurring role of Russian cultural attach\u00e9, Valeria Poriskova.<ref>{{cite web|last=Petski|first=Denise|title=\u2018Designated Survivor\u2019: Nora Zehetner Set To Recur On ABC Drama Series|url=http://deadline.com/2018/03/designated-survivor-nora-zehetner-recur-abc-drama-series-1202346189/|date=March 19, 2018|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=March 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180322021914/http://deadline.com/2018/03/designated-survivor-nora-zehetner-recur-abc-drama-series-1202346189/|archive-date=March 22, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Ratings==\n{{Television episode ratings\n| width    = 99\n\n| title1   = [[#ep22|One Year In]]\n| date1    = September 27, 2017\n| rs1      = 1.1/4\n| viewers1 = 5.50<ref name=\"2.01\"/>\n| dvr1     = 1.4\n| dvrv1    = 5.84\n| total1   = 2.5\n| totalv1  = 11.34<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/dvr-ratings/broadcast-live-7-ratings-sept-25-oct-1-2017/|title='This Is Us' and 'The Good Doctor' score big in premiere week broadcast Live +7 ratings|last=Porter|first=Rick|date=October 13, 2017|work=TV by the Numbers|accessdate=October 13, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171014174621/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/dvr-ratings/broadcast-live-7-ratings-sept-25-oct-1-2017/|archive-date=October 14, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n| title2   = [[#ep23|Sting of the Tail]]\n| date2    = October 4, 2017\n| rs2      = 0.9/4\n| viewers2 = 4.80<ref name=\"2.02\"/>\n| dvr2     = 1.2\n| dvrv2    = 5.20\n| total2   = 2.1\n| totalv2  = 10.00<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/dvr-ratings/week-2-broadcast-live-7-ratings-oct-2-8-2017/|title='The Orville,' 'Once Upon a Time,' 5 more shows double in week 2 broadcast Live +7 ratings|last=Porter|first=Rick|date=Octo